+"""Latched control state for ExecHealth auto-freeze / operator thaw.
 
-P7/P8 purpose
--------------
-P5/P6 introduced a raw auto-freeze key that hard-blocks publish/entry paths.
-That key alone is operationally weak because deleting it can thaw the system
-without any audit trail. P7 added a *latched* control/state layer. P8 hardens
-that flow further:
-
-- every autoguard trigger creates a pending ack nonce
-- operator thaw must provide the exact pending nonce (compare-and-set)
-- thaw writes a signed ack into control/state and into an audit event stream
-- control/state deletion without a valid ack-event can be detected separately
+P7/P8 introduced a latched control layer with signed operator ack. P9 upgrades
+that thaw path to a strict two-phase / dual-control workflow:
+
+1. prepare thaw request (request_id + nonce CAS)
+2. second operator approves it
+3. approved operator emits final signed commit event
+
+The runtime hook only accepts thaw when the dual-control commit signature is
+valid. Legacy single-operator thaw can be disabled globally and is disabled by
+default in P9.
 """
 
